plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Huddersfield Town F.C.|Huddersfield Town]].
==Club career== Grant was top scorer for Charlton Athletic U18s during the 2012–13 and 2013–14 seasons while still a schoolboy.<ref name="Jimmy Stone">{{cite web|url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/20140923-karlan-ahearne-grant-deal-1936350.aspx|title=Highly-rated striker Karlan Ahearne-Grant agrees long-term deal to stay with the club|author=Jimmy Stone|work=cafc.co.uk}}</ref> Less than a week after his 17th birthday, on 23 September 2014, Grant signed a three-year contract with Charlton.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefa.com/news/england/development/2014/sep/karlan-ahearne-grant-signs-three-year-deal-with-charlton-athletic-270914|title=England U17 international Karlan Ahearne-Grant celebrates first pro deal with inclusion in Charlton Athletic's matchday squad – England – The FA|author=The Football Association|work=thefa.com}}</ref> He made his professional debut shortly after on 30 September 2014, as an 89th-minute substitute in a 1–0 victory against [[Norwich City F.C.|Norwich City]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29320492|title=Norwich City 0–1 Charlton Athletic|publisher=BBC Sport|date=30 September 2014|accessdate=11 October 2014}}</ref> He later made his first start on 18 October 2014 in a 1–0 loss against [[A.F.C. Bournemouth|AFC Bournemouth]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/29579623|title=BBC Sport – Bournemouth 1–0 Charlton Athletic|author=Mark Mitchener|work=BBC Sport}}</ref> He scored his first competitive goal for the Addicks first team in a 4–1 [[Football League Cup]] win over [[Dagenham & Redbridge F.C.|Dagenham & Redbridge]].<ref>[https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/33769182 "Charlton Athletic 4–1 Dagenham & Redbridge"] BBC Sport. 11 August 2015. Retrieved 12 August 2015.</ref> On 26 September, he scored his first league goal for Charlton in a 2–1 loss to [[Cardiff City]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Cardiff 2–1 Charlton|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34299142|accessdate=28 September 2015|publisher=BBC Sport|date=26 September 2015}}</ref>
On 30 January 2018, Grant joined [[Crawley Town F.C.|Crawley Town]] on loan until the end of the 2017–18 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Karlan Ahearne-Grant makes League Two loan switch|url=https://www.cafc.co.uk/news/view/5a7066e47a90a/karlan-ahearne-grant-makes-league-two-loan-switch|accessdate=30 January 2018|publisher=Charlton Athletic official website|date=30 January 2018}}</ref>
===Huddersfield Town=== On 30 January 2019, Grant joined [[Huddersfield Town A.F.C.|Huddersfield Town]] for an undisclosed fee, signing a contract until the summer of 2022 with the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.htafc.com/news/2019/january/transfer-karlan-grant-joins-huddersfield-town/|title=TRANSFER: KARLAN GRANT JOINS HUDDERSFIELD TOWN!|publisher=Huddersfield Town|accessdate=30 January 2019}}</ref> He made his debut for the Yorkshire club three days later in a 5–0 away loss to [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] where he came on as a substitute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47011453|title=Chelsea 5–0 Huddersfield Town|publisher=BBC Sport|date=2 February 2019|accessdate=2 February 2019}}</ref> On 9 February 2019 Grant scored his first Huddersfield goal on his second Town appearance in a 2-1 home loss against [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/47099273|title=FA Cup: Huddersfield Town 1-2 Arsenal|publisher=BBC Sport|date=9 February 2019|accessdate=9 February 2019}}</ref>
==International career== In February 2014, Grant represented [[England national under-17 football team|England U17]] in the Algarve tournament.<ref name="Jimmy Stone"/> On 6 November 2014, Grant was called up to the [[England national under-18 football team|England U18]] squad for a double header against Poland.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cafc.co.uk/news/article/20141106-ahearne-grant-earns-england-u18-call-up-2067787.aspx|title=Charlton Athletic: Karlan Ahearne-Grant earns England U18 call-up|author=Iain Liddle|work=cafc.co.uk}}</ref> He played for [[England national under-19 football team|England U19]] in September 2015, against Croatia.<ref>{{Cite web | title = Josh Onomah bags equaliser as England hold hosts Croatia | publisher = The FA | date = 7 September 2015 | accessdate = 14 June 2018 | url = http://www.thefa.com/news/2015/sep/07/match-report-croatia-v-england-u19s-070915}}</ref>
==Personal life== In June 2018, whilst on holiday in [[Ibiza]], Grant and fellow teammate [[Reeco Hackett-Fairchild]] were arrested on suspicion of a [[sexual assault]] on a 19-year-old woman.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Muro |first1=Giuseppe |title=Charlton striker Reeco Hackett-Fairchild to miss training as probe into alleged sexual assault goes on |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/sport/football/charlton-striker-reeco-hackettfairchild-to-miss-training-as-probe-into-alleged-sexual-assault-goes-a3872571.html |accessdate=28 June 2018 |work=[[Evening Standard]] |date=26 June 2018}}</ref>
In the summer of 2018, he dropped the Ahearne part of his surname, to become known as Karlan Grant.<ref>{{Cite web |title=QPR 3-3 Charlton Athletic |first=Chris |last=Thompson |work=Kent Sports News |date=7 July 2018 |accessdate=12 September 2018 |url= http://www.kentsportsnews.com/qpr-3-3-charlton-athletic-07-07-2018/}}</ref>
